description: Hello big world! When you're as little as I am, everything is big. And scary. name: Curly
Pirelli
Dave
description: Dave is a social butterfly who loves to play and snuggle in close to his people, and has never met a human he didn't like. On top of being Mr. Popular, he'd also make a great candidate for Class Clown with his enthusiastic and playful nature. He loves to go on walks and romps with his friends at the shelter and then settle in for some serious cuddle time and scritches. Dave has lived in a home before and picked up some impressive manners. He walks nicely on leash, is fully house-trained and sleeps quietly through the night in his crate. He can also be left home without issue for eight-hour stretches. Although he hasn't lived with children, he has been noted to be playful, tolerant and easygoing with kids over the age of 6 that he's interacted with. He's lived successfully with a dog before, and as long as feeding time is properly managed, he should do okay with a well-matched doggie sibling. Dave is also in APA!'s Total Obedience Program. The Total Obedience Program (TOP) is modeled after the AKC's Canine Good Citizen (CGC) test. As a TOP dog, Dave has a personalized training plan and works with a volunteer trainer several times a week to help him learn the skills to become the best dog he can be! Dave is learning skills like sit and down, walking nicely on leash, sitting calmly when approached by strangers or other dogs, staying in a sit or down until told "free," coming when called and "Place", which means he will go to a specific place in your home on command. Once he successfully completes all the skills on his training plan, Dave will be considered TOP Dog Ready! Dave is working hard to become a wonderful companion, and as a part of APA's Total Obedience Program you can work with APA staff to continue to build a training relationship with Dave after adoption and master all the TOP dog skills together. Check out a video on APA's CGC program, on which the TOP was based: https://vimeo.com/89434193 Obedient and eager to please, Dave would be a great fit for any number of loving homes. Come meet this sweet boy and see if he's perfect for yours!

name: Sandia
Peach
description: Peach is such a social butterfly! She loves all people she meets - and especially the ones she's living with. She jumps with excitement when she hears that they're praising her, and she wants to be close to them and get their petting and belly rubs. She also loves making friends with dogs, a little shy at first and then wanting to play all day. And she's even interested in cats she sees on the long walks she enjoys every day. At her foster home, this playful girl loves running in the yard, playing with dog buddies who come visit and chasing flying bugs. Then she'll play with her chew toys and enjoy taking naps in her doggy bed, falling asleep on her back with her legs open. So adorable! She already understands "sit" and is working on her manners, learning to pause her jumping. She's also house-trained and sleeps in her crate overnight. And she does well there when her fosters are away. This sweet, energetic girl will love a home with parents who can take her for those walks she loves and continue her training. She'll also enjoy a lively doggie playmate. Come meet this butterfly. Offer her a walk and she'll stroll home with you!

description: If you are looking for a friend to join you on your adventures, look no further than this charming girl, Punkin. She is just a baby, but you can already see that she is up for fun and action. She loves playing with her three brothers and two sisters. In foster care, they had an interesting birth. Their momma went under a shed to give birth and refused to bring them out - until a rainy downpour came and their foster mom rescued all of them from flooding, moving them into the house. Now, her siblings follow her around just to see what fun she is going to discover. She also loves finding a favorite toy, getting in a soft bed, and giving the toy a good chew. She is an extra pretty little thing with a soft coat. Her special talent is getting and giving kisses. The little sweetie is happy and healthy, and she has a lovely, balanced personality. She is very loving and enjoys being cuddled. This lovable little lass is a prize and is going to make someone the best "Good Girl" ever. Come meet this charming doll today!

name: Purity
description: Purity was born to a very loving and attentive mother, in her foster mom's home. She is a well-adjusted, curious and sweet puppy who loves to be loved. She is a smart and obedient young puppy who loves to play with her sister and chew toys, and she also loves to chase her foster mom when outside. She is very friendly and loves to be held, petted and played with. She has the cutest fat little paws and is a decent size for a young girl. It's unknown how big she'll end up or what breed she'll look like. Her mother is a 20 lb. terrier/pit mix. She's the perfect candidate for genetic testing if you're curious. Purity isn't super hyper. She plays at a normal pace and eats in a relaxed way. Her mother LOVES walks, and she's likely to enjoy that too once she's older. Like her mother, she really pays attention to her surroundings. She'll look up and around and sniff her surroundings. She's just discovered how the wind will blow the leaves on trees and she's fascinated! She already comes when called. Purity will do great in a home where she can feel safe and loved. Keeping her occupied with toys and walks (once she's vaccinated and old enough) will be important. Like her very loving mother, Purity will be a great companion and a beautiful dog. If you're up for offering consistent training in a loving, calm home, Purity is your girl. Her foster loves her very much and cannot wait to help find her life partner!

He will recharge by catching quick a cat nap, preferably on a heating pad, and then he's ready to join the scrum again! Hood River is part of a modern blended family! He grew up with two other litters in his foster home, and they are one big happy family. They also grew up around two resident adult cats and a dog, so they definitely know how to get along in a big family! If you are considering adopting a pair, please ask us about this amazing family, and we can suggest the perfect pair for you. They are all adorable and love each other! Hood River has the most captivating face and the most beautiful spotted orange tabby "leopard" coat. No matter how you look at him, you are going to want to pick him up and love on him; contact us today to arrange a meet & greet! name: Mona
description:
Will you be Mona's HERO??

If you'd really like to RESCUE a dog and really make a huge difference consider a Mona. She is far from perfect but who's perfect anyway? She has such a gentle, kind spirit. She LOVES walks and car rides. She has some medical issues but they are totally manageable. They have prevented her from getting adopted. Don't let that stop you from adopting her!!

Here's her back story:
We agreed to take Mona in when she was only eight-weeks-old. She was a very sick little puppy. She had daily seizures and was completely incontinent.

Since that time, many years ago, her epilepsy is managed well and the incontinence is almost completely gone. She only has occasional accidents overnight but we think that's more due to being stubborn about going outside to potty the last time at night, not because of incontinence. So making sure she goes outside to go potty around 10:00 p.m. would solve that likely.
Her seizures are controlled with medication and the bladder surgery took care of her leaking mostly. She is on medication for the incontinence which really helps!

For a dog who had a grim future it's truly amazing how far she's come. Now all we have to worry about with Mona is finding her the best possible family that can love her as she is...not quite perfect but so incredibly darling.

A tenacious, independent, confident, mischievous, joyful and sensitive husky, that's our Mona. She is a bit protective when she's in her cage so we think a family with small kids wouldn't be right for her.

Mona loves to play in water and would love a baby pool in her yard in the summertime. She loves walks so much and is both affectionate when she wants attention and aloof at times too, which is being what huskies can be!

She loves the snow, her crate, and her nylabones. She is very smart and sensitive too.

Mona co-exists with other dogs and can even play with another dog if they other dog is pushy about play but otherwise she lives without issue with other dogs. She is not good with cats or small critters.

She lives with a family with a eight-year-old child. But she would be best in a family with kids over ten only because she can get a bit protective around her cage when she steals something and brings it into the cage with her. Yes, Mona can be naughty...but not too naughty"":)

Mona is on medication for her seizures and incontinence. The total cost is roughly $100.00 a month. Because of her medications she needs quarterly blood tests. Additional medical expenses should be anticipated and money set aside just in case.

A home visit will be required to adopt Mona so please only adoption applications within an hour of Libertyville, IL.
_________________________________________________________________________
Adoption Donation for Mona is $ 425.00

WANT TO MEET Mona

The first step would be for you to go to our website at www.aear.org and then to the “Adopting a Pet” page to read about our Adoption Process which will answer many of your questions and then to fill out an Adoption Application.

Also, please visit our very active Facebook Page for updates on Mona and our other adoptable pets with AEAR - www.facebook.com/aear.org

All our animals available for adoption are living in foster homes. This gives us the ability to really get to know the animals we have available and find them families that are a good fit for them based on their personalities. We do not have a shelter to visit the animals.

Hunter Miska is an Maraican profession ice hockey goaltender. Pasadena Humane's Miska has probably never played ice hockey. Miska is a beautiful Siberian Husky whose owner decided not to keep due to her escaping the yard. Huskies are generally known to be busy dogs and need to be kept busy. If they get bored, Huskies tend to go looking for an adventure. Savvy Husky owners find games and toys to keep their dogs busy, take them on lots of walks to address the energy, and give them lots of attention and love. Miska is probably no exception to the rule. While a little unsure of being in a shelter, she is generally well-behaved and overall friendly to our staff. Our staff has discovered that Miska needs a bit more leash training . . . you know, for all those walks she should be getting! And now she needs just the right home! She is a young six years which qualifies her for our Seniors for Seniors Program. This means if an adopter is sixty years old or more, then her adoption is FREE!

Learn more about our adoption process.

Meet Milo JuM
 
Milo is a pretty common name, right??  I mean, no one famous by that name, right?
Wait.. wait a minute!!!   VENUS DE MILO!!!! YES, I am, of course, the MALE Venus de Milo :)!!   I am a HANDSOME boy with a mysterious air about me too. I mean, why did she not have any ARMS?? A mystery for sure!  I love to be loved and I love to give love too! Just like the Greek goddess of love (v-d-m), I am a canine version.
 
I am also a lucky fella! I was left by my "owners" when they moved... along with my friends Magnus and Samantha... We don't know WHY they left us but we all got saved together and that is the icing on the proverbial cake!  I am a gorgeous catahoula mixed boy, I have the hint of blue eye and the catahoula markings that make me look really great!
 
I am about 48# and 6 yrs old, I am great with other dogs and people.   
I want a realy realy super responsible family who will take me WITH them if they ever move!
I will promise to love you forever ever ever more and give you joy the rest of your lives too. 
Look me up and apply to adopt me soon, cause Venus De Milo is waiting!!!
 
So if you would like me to join your family.... please email Adoptions@Godsdogsrescue.org and tell them you want ME... MILO!!!

GOD'S DOGS Rescue, in San Antonio TX, does not have a shelter - ALL of our dogs are raised in foster homes in the San Antonio area. Each dog comes spayed or neutered, up-to-date on vaccinations that are appropriate for their age, microchipped, heartworm tested and on current on monthly flea/tick and heartworm preventative.

ALL OF THIS IS INCLUDED IN THE ADOPTION FEE OF $250.00 FOR PUPPIES LOCAL (Local is in the state of Texas) and LOCAL ADULTS are $200 and Medical records will come with each dog at the time of adoption.  IF THIS IS AN OUT OF STATE ADOPTION, TRANSPORT TO YOU is included in the adoption fee of $500.00 for PUPPIES and $400.00 for ADULTS. We transport all over the country!!

All our dogs are socialized and we try to provide you a good understanding of the dog’s personality. Please visit our website, www.godsdogsrescue.org for more information about what we do;  You will also find helpful information about transport, our adoption application and pictures of our all our dogs/pups looking for homes!!

Please contact us at info@godsdogsrescue.org for more information about adopting one of our dogs and puppies or fill out an adoption application at http://www.godsdogsrescue.org/adopt/adoption-application/

Our page offers information about adoption, volunteering, fostering and TRANSPORT to YOU! 

Thank you for wanting to adopt a rescued dog, their LIVES depend on it!


 

Hope to meet you soon!!!

                                           www.godsdogsrescue.org
